# Braindump test file (2026-05-02)
## Purpose
### Stress-test every token, every depth, every grammar trap

This file is the canonical test for the braindump grammar and palette.
Every section below either confirms a token works (POSITIVE) or confirms
a thing-that-looks-like-a-token does NOT match (NEGATIVE / TRAP).


# ============================================================
# POSITIVE: Whole-line markers (depth 1 → 2 → 3)
# ============================================================

# Heading depth 1
## Heading depth 2
### Heading depth 3

= Category depth 1
== Category depth 2
=== Category depth 3

+ Section depth 1
++ Section depth 2
+++ Section depth 3

? question depth 1
?? question depth 2
??? question depth 3

! alert single depth (no repetition by design)


# ============================================================
# POSITIVE: Marker-only (text after marker stays default)
# ============================================================

- bullet depth 1
-- bullet depth 2
--- bullet depth 3

* important depth 1
** important depth 2
*** important depth 3

> forward depth 1
>> forward depth 2
>>> forward depth 3

< back depth 1
<< back depth 2
<<< back depth 3


