# ============================================================
# POSITIVE: Realistic indented note
# ============================================================

# Build pipeline
    high level: Plan, Build, Ship
    + project
        (the whole repo)
        - needs planning
            > harness Plan project:<path/to/brief>
            output: stories, ordered
        ? do we version the brief
        ! deadline before kickoff
    + story
        (in existing codebase)
        - break down into tasks
            > harness Plan story:<path/to/brief>
        // TODO: confirm dependency graph format
    + task
        (smallest unit, ready for implementation)
        - has acceptance criteria
        - has test plan

## Build phases (per task)
    preflight    < create branch, set up env
    spec         < design, UI needs, storybook, e2e
    context      ? does spec need context
    code         < write the implementation
    tests        < unit + integration in parallel
    gates        < tsc, eslint, vitest, a11y
    commit       < locally only, no push


# ============================================================
# POSITIVE: Q&A pattern from real notes
# ============================================================

Q1: How do you break down a feature for a small team?
    - slice vertically, end-to-end early
    - de-risk unknowns first
    - milestones around user value
    ? are there hidden dependencies
    ! protect 20% buffer time
    // came up in 1:1 last week

Q2: When do you escalate vs decide?
    - default is to decide
    Escalate when:
        - irreversible (db choice, contracts)
        - crosses team boundaries
        - cost of being wrong is high
    < came up in design review
    > follow up with @alice next week


